snippet.textDisplay:
Heading to Hunza at 12am in the night with almost 8 hours already spent in travel and extremely tired and half alseep, this song came on in the bus while I was feeling so calm and moving side to side with the bus movement. The song was so soothing I almost forgot I was in a bus. It was unlike anything I've felt before, so serene. And me being an uncultured person that I am, while listening closely to lyrics even in that sleepy state, could not understand what the song meant. It wasn't until the part 'yaar nu milay gi aj laash yaar di' where I suddenly opened my eyes like what happened, why are you so hurt? Only after realizing the whole story I understood the song was a tragic story and a conversation between her and the ghara.

Undoubtedly this is a song that I'll forever remember, and it has been associated with the unmatched peace that I felt on that day, absolutely outside any worries of the daily life and job cycle. Just the presence of being. What a beautiful and moving composition.
